sql:
SELECT year_label, start_date, end_date, year_id
FROM academic_years
WHERE year_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Performance variation refers to the difference between the highest and lowest performance metrics achieved by a student in different departments;
- Attendance variation refers to the difference between the highest and lowest attendance rates of a student across departments;
- Overall performance and attendance records imply average metrics across all departments for each student.
